 The year is 1953. A visiting archaeologist 
 called Varun Shrivastav comes to the       
 village of Manikpur in West Bengal to      
 excavate the temple grounds of the local   
 Zamindar. With knowledge and experience    
 beyond his young demeanour, Varun greatly  
 impresses the Zamindar and his family.     
 Especially Pakhi, the Zamindar's feisty    
 and only daughter, who finds herself       
 irrevocably drawn towards him. But Varun   
 isn't all he seems on the surface. And as  
 the simmering attraction between him and   
 Pakhi leads to a tender and deep love, he  
 is forced to choose between her and his    
 past. Making his choice, Varun disappears.
